Background

		Ms. Christine Lynn Hurtsellers, CFA, has been the Chief Executive Officer at Voya Investment Management LLC since September 1, 2016. Ms. Hurtsellers serves as Chief Investment Officer of Fixed Income and Portfolio Manager at Voya Investment Management Co. LLC. She serves as Portfolio Manager of Transamerica Series Trust - Transamerica Voya Limited Maturity Bond VP. She serves as Chief Investment Officer of Fixed Income and Portfolio Manager of ING Series Fund - ING Balanced ... Fund. She has been the Chief Executive Officer of Investment Management Business at Voya Financial, Inc. since September 1, 2016. She serves as Chief Investment Officer of Fixed Income and Head of Public Fixed Income at ING Investment Management Americas. Ms. Hurtsellers has a vast investment experience. She served as Portfolio Manager of Voya Variable Product Funds - Voya Intermediate Bond Portfolio since January 2009. Ms. Hurtsellers served as the Head of Structured Finance, Executive Vice President and Portfolio Manager at Voya Investment Management and also served as its Chief Investment Officer of Fixed Income since 2009 and also served on a mortgage-backed securities team that was responsible for its proprietary mortgage derivatives portfolios. She joined Voya Investment Management in 2004 as a Senior Portfolio Manager. Prior to this, Ms. Hurtsellers led the agency-guaranteed retained portfolio team at the Federal Home Loan Mortgage Corporation. She was also a Portfolio Manager responsible for mortgages and structured products at Alliance Capital Management and Banc One and a Client Consultant at Pentalpha Capital group. She served as the Chief Investment Officer of Fixed Income and Portfolio Manager of various funds in the fund complex of ING Funds/Voya Funds. She serves as a Director at Voya Investment Management Co. LLC. She serves as a Board Member of Pomona Capital and ING Series Fund - ING Balanced Fund. She served as a Director of various funds in the fund complex of ING Funds/Voya Funds. Ms. Hurtsellers serves on the Board of Councilors for the Carter Center and has served on the Advisory Board for the Kennesaw University Collegiate Recovery Program. She holds the Chartered Financial Analyst designation. Ms. Hurtsellers received a B.A. in Finance with high honors from Indiana University Kelley School of Business.Read Full Background




